"""
Workflow 08 — Finetune Pangolin on SF3B1 SSU data and evaluate.

Pangolin (Zeng & Bromberg 2022) is a dilated-residual CNN with a 10 kb context
window, operating at 5 kb output resolution.  We replace its 4-tissue heads with
fresh [2-class, 1-sigmoid] heads for each (sample, strand) condition and finetune
using the same SF3B1 SSU data and fold splits as AlphaGenome (workflow 05).

NOTE on splits: Pangolin's backbone was pretrained with chromosome-based splits
(even chrs = train, odd chrs = test), independent of AlphaGenome's FOLD_1 BED
splits.  For downstream finetuning we use AlphaGenome's FOLD_1 train/val BEDs
for both models so the comparison is fair.

NOTE on editable install: before running this workflow, install custom-pangolin
into the alphagenome_pytorch conda environment once:
    conda run -n alphagenome_pytorch pip install -e src/custom-pangolin

Run with:
    snakemake -s workflows/08-finetune_pangolin/Snakefile --use-conda [-n]
"""

import os

configfile: "config/config.yaml"

include: "rules/intervals.smk"
include: "rules/dev.smk"
include: "rules/full.smk"


rule all:
    input:
        rules.all_dev.input,
        rules.all_full.input,
